# 
outliers_idx = {}
for feature in log_data.keys():
    
    # TODOQ125th
    Q1 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 25, axis=0)
    
    # TODOQ375th
    Q3 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 75, axis=0)
    
    # TODO1.5
    step = (Q3 - Q1) * 1.5
    
    # 
    print "Data points considered outliers for the feature '{}':".format(feature)
    #print "Q1 - step: ",Q1 - step
    #print "Q3 + step: ",Q3 + step
    outliers_all = log_data[~((log_data[feature] >= Q1 - step) & (log_data[feature] <= Q3 + step))]
    outliers_idx[feature] = outliers_all.index
    display(log_data[~((log_data[feature] >= Q1 - step) & (log_data[feature] <= Q3 + step))])

for i in range(2,11):
    clusterer_test = KMeans(n_clusters=i,random_state=123).fit(reduced_data)
    preds_test = clusterer_test.predict(reduced_data)
    score_test = silhouette_score(reduced_data, preds_test, metric='euclidean', random_state=123 )
    score_tests[i] = score_test
    i += 1
score_tests

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# 
cluster_data = pd.read_csv("cluster.csv")
y = cluster_data['Region']
X = cluster_data.drop(['Region'], axis = 1)

# 
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.8, random_state=24)

clf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=24)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
print "cluster", clf.score(X_test, y_test)

# cluster
X_train = X_train.copy()
X_train.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
X_test = X_test.copy()
X_test.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
print "cluster", clf.score(X_test, y_test)
